    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170737>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5–8. Glyptothrips arkansanus, female lectotype and paralectotypes. (5) Female. (6) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–V. (7) Abdominal segments VII–X, dorsal view. (8) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a narrow transverse band medially." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170753>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–18. Glyptothrips claviger, female holotype and paratypes. (14) Female. (15) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–III; OC—occipital setae. (16) Abdominal segments VI–X. (17) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a large plate covering most of the sternite. (18) Antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170753/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170800>
    dc:description "FIGURES 57–60. Glyptothrips saltuarius, female holotype. (57) Female. (58) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–III. (59) Abdominal segments VII–X. (60) Antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170800/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170784>
    dc:description "FIGURES 41–46. Glyptothrips interior, male paratype. (41) Male. (42) Head and prothorax; fore tarsal tooth indicated by arrow heads. OC—occipital setae, PO—postocular setae, POC—postocellar setae. (43) Antenna. (44) Pterothorax and abdominal segments I–III. (45) Abdominal segments VIII–X, with tergite IX setae indicated. (46) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a narrow transverse band subbasally (arrow head)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170784/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170759>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–24. Glyptothrips divergens, female and male paratypes. (19) Female. (20) Head and pronotum; PO—postocular setae. (21) Thorax and abdominal segments I–III; VL—ventrolateral setae. (22) Abdominal segments VI–X. (23) Antenna. (24) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a transverse ellipse medially." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170774>
    dc:description "FIGURES 31–36. Glyptothrips fuscipes, female holotype and male paratype. (31) Female. (32) Head, pro- and mesonotum.(33) Thorax, mid and hind legs, and abdominal segments I–IV. (34) Abdominal segments V–X. (35) Antenna. (36) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a large plate covering most of the sternite. ACS—antennal capitate setae; FT—femoral thickened setae; VL—ventrolateral setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170774/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170810>
    dc:description "FIGURES 66–73. Glyptothrips subcalvus, female holotype, female paratype, and male non-types. (66) Female. (67) Head and forelegs. (68) Antenna. (69) Thorax and pelta; VL—ventrolateral setae. (70–72) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, showing variation in size and form between different males. (73) Abdominal segments VI–X." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170810/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170806>
    dc:description "FIGURES 61–65. Glyptothrips silvaticus, female holotype. (61) Female. (62) Head, thorax and pelta; VL—ventrolateral setae. (63) Foreleg; FT—femoral thickened setae. (64) Antenna. (65) Abdominal segments VII–X." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170806/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170765>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25–27. Glyptothrips flavescens, female holotype and female paratype. (25) Female. (26) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–IV. (27) Abdominal segments VI–X." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170788>
    dc:description "FIGURES 47–50. Glyptothrips longiceps, female holotype. (47) Female. (48) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–III; fore tarsal tooth indicated by arrow head. FT—femoral thickened setae. (49) Abdominal segments VI–X. (50) Antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170788/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170747>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9–13. Glyptothrips bucca, female holotype and male allotype. (9) Female. (10) Head, thorax, and abdominal segments I–III. (11) Abdominal segments VI–X. (12) Antenna. (13) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a circular plate medially." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170747/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170769>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28–30. Glyptothrips floridensis, male from type series. (28) Male. (29) Head and prothorax. (30) Abdominal segments VI–X, ventral view; sternite VIII with a subbasal pore plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170769/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170778>
    dc:description "FIGURES 37–40. Glyptothrips hylaeus, male holotype. (37) Male. (38) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–III. (39) Abdominal segments VII–X. (40) Male pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII, a large plate covering most of the sternite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170778/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10170794>
    dc:description "FIGURES 51–56. Glyptothrips reticulatus, female and male paratypes. (51) Male. (52) Female. (53) Head and pronotum. (54) Antenna. (55) Head, thorax and abdominal segments I–II. (56) Abdominal segments VI–X." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10170794/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

